<description>Olof began his career in the domestic league at Degerfors in the 1996 season. After only one season he moved to AIK Solna where he came to the attention of Spanish club Racing Santender for whom he signed in the October 1998.
Olef made his debut for Sweden in February 2000 against Italy and went on to win a place in the squad for the Euro 2000 finals, featuring in each of his country's three matches.
He became a regular in the Swedish national team and his performances bought him to the attention of Premiership side Aston Villa whom he joined in the 2001 close season for ï¿½7 million. He fitted in well replacing Gareth Southgate at the heart of the defence and was seen as a key player for Sweden at the 2002 World Cup Finals.
 Olof signed a new four-year contract with Aston Villa in May 2004.</description>

